::: center-text
### Welcome! I'm Shreyas Meher. This site showcases my work in computational linguistics and political analysis. Feel free to explore and connect with me!
:::

### Research Interests

> Large Language Models (LLMs), Internet Censorship, Developmental Economics, Political Conflict, and Violence

### Currently at

> **The University of Texas at Dallas** <br> **Research Assistant** <br> *ConfliBERT Project with [Dr. Patrick Brandt](https://personal.utdallas.edu/~pxb054000/) (2022-present)* <br> [Dr. Pengfei Zhang](https://pengfei-zhang.com/) (2022-present) <br> [Dr. Lauren Pinson](https://www.lpinson.com/) (2021) <br> [Dr. Jonas Bunte](https://jonasbunte.com/) (2020)

> **Teaching Assistant** <br> *[Dr. Vito D'Orazio](https://vitodorazio.org/) (2020-2021)* <br> [Dr. Richard Scotch](https://profiles.utdallas.edu/richard.scotch)

### Key Projects

> **ConfliBERT Research Lab** <br> A groundbreaking project exploring political conflict and violence using pre-trained language models. [Learn More](https://github.com/eventdata/ConfliBERT)

> **Dissertation on Censorship in Democracies and Autocracies** <br> An in-depth analysis focusing on electoral accountability with case studies in India and China. 
